{'book': {'publisher': 'Penguin Books', 'synopsis': "Look out for a new book from Garry Wills, What The Qur'an Meant, coming fall 2017.<br/><br/>Pulitzer Prize winner Garry Wills brings the same fresh scholarship, lively prose, and critical appreciation that characterize his well-known books on religion and American history to this outstanding biography of one of the most influential Christian philosophers.<br/><br/>Saint Augustine follows its subject from his youth in fourth-century Africa to his conversion and subsequent development as a theologian. It challenges the widely held misconceptions about Augustine’s sexual excesses and shows how, in embracing classical philosophy, Augustine managed to enlist “pagan authors” in the defense of Christianity. The result is a biography that makes a spiritual ancestor feel like our contemporary.", 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/59/85/9780143035985.jpg', 'title_long': 'Saint Augustine: A Life (Penguin Lives Biographies)', 'edition': 'Reprint', 'dimensions': 'Height: 7.1 Inches, Length: 5.1 Inches, Weight: 0.29982867632 Pounds, Width: 0.44 Inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 5.1}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.44}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.29982867632}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 7.1}}, 'pages': 176, 'date_published': '2005-08-30', 'subjects': ['Christian Books & Bibles', 'Churches & Church Leadership', 'Church History', 'History', 'Biographies & Memoirs', 'Leaders & Notable People', 'Religious', 'Professionals & Academics', 'Philosophers', 'World', 'Religion & Spirituality', 'Religious Studies', 'Philosophy', 'Self Service', 'Custom Stores'], 'authors': ['Garry Wills'], 'title': 'Saint Augustine: A Life (Penguin Lives Biographies)', 'isbn13': '9780143035985', 'msrp': 15, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isbn': '0143035983', 'isbn10': '0143035983'}}